                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Just one more programmer&apos;s opinion here, but while I agree 100% with the statement that the word &lt;code&gt;using&lt;/code&gt; should never appear in a header, I&apos;m not as convinced about the free license to place &lt;code&gt;using namespace xyz;&lt;/code&gt; anywhere in your code, especially if &lt;code&gt;xyz&lt;/code&gt; is &lt;code&gt;std&lt;/code&gt;.  I use the &lt;code&gt;using std::vector;&lt;/code&gt; form, since that only pulls a single element from the namespace into pseudo-global scope, therefore leading to far less risk of a collision.&lt;/span&gt;

