                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;The real problem here is that C++ still has namespace-less globals.  This, and the fact that &apos;this&apos; is implicit in methods, causes so many bugs and problems I can&apos;t even count them, even with the right &apos;count&apos; variable. ;)&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/3308532/aiken-drum&quot; title=&quot;561 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Aiken Drum&lt;/a&gt;
